                            <comment id="205976" author="pjones" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2017 13:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You will need to contact the central Intel Customer Support channels to get assistance for this offering - support.intel.com&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="205870" author="bhushanvc" created="Mon, 21 Aug 2017 13:10:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Peter,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes. Exactly we have installed Lustre Client File System on Separate EC2 Instance(Server) which contains MGS, MDT, OSS, etc. We have Created a Separate EC2 RHEL Instance . We have Installed Lustre Client on that RHEL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are trying to WRITE from Lustre Client to Lustre File System But we are not getting any Idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please help us.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="205867" author="pjones" created="Mon, 21 Aug 2017 13:02:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi there&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This JIRA project is for tracking work relating to the Lustre Community releases of Lustre. It sounds like you are trying to use Lustre on AWS and have some questions relating to that. Any such qiestions can be answered via the support channels provided for that offering (as long as you have selected the support option when setting up your Lustre filesystem)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
